Rustenburg farm attack, traumatized family assaulted, tied with wire  These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More  A family has been terribly traumatised after a violent farm attack on a farm in Boshoek outside Rustenburg in the North West. The attack took place at about 03:00 on the morning of 23 April 2018. Three armed blacks surprised a 26 year old man while he was asleep in bed. His pregnant wife, one year old child and another eleven year old child were tied up with wire. Two .22 firearms, money and cellphones were robbed during the ordeal. The attackers inflicted serious injuries on the family. After the attackers left the wife managed to get free and summon help. There is no further information at this stage and names have been withheld at this point. The police are on the scene investigating. Read the original article in Afrikaans on BKA Boere Krisis Aksie  Close Modal Close Modal           These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. Family-Friendly Content
